THREE thugs who were bust while driving around with fake number plates will be spending Christmas behind bars.They were arrested on Tuesday by cops who spotted the black BMW in Merebank, south of Durban. When the police searched the car, they recovered two unlicensed firearms and ammunition. They immediately arrested the three men travelling in the car. Police spokeswoman Captain Nqobile Gwala said the three suspects &ndash; aged between 26 and 43 &ndash; appeared in the Wentworth Magistrates Court on Wednesday and were kept in custody. &ldquo;They were charged with possession of unlicensed firearms and ammunition. They will be back in court on Thursday for a bail application,&rdquo; she said.Gwala said cops were following up on information on Himalayas Road in Merebank when they spotted the suspicious black BMW with three occupants. &ldquo;The vehicle had false plates and when the police searched it, they found two unlicensed firearms on two suspects. They were both charged with possession of a firearm without a licence. &ldquo;The third suspect was found in possession of five rounds of live ammunition. The recovered firearms will be sent for ballistic testing.&rdquo; KZN acting provincial commissioner Major-General Bheki Langa praised the Umhlali K9 unit for their good work in arresting the suspects and recovering the firearms. &ldquo;We will continue to deploy our members to each and every corner of the province during the festive season. We want to make sure our people have a safe and happy time over this period.&rdquo;